  <section class='inverse monospace'>
    <h3>Advice for working responsive</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Find a prototyping tool you're comfortable working with so you can test responsive states without a developer.</li>
      <li>Avoid the waste of <em>over-comping</em>. Trying to maintain 2-3 alternate views for each screen you're designing for can become a productivity sinkhole.</li>
      <li>Evaluating work on a artboard won't provide the same insights as a browser or mobile phone.</li>
      <li>Don't design in <em>waterfall</em>; designing an entire screen in one form-factor and then moving on to the next. Instead, focus on one form factor but stop every once and awhile and consider the implications for responsive states.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

